**Abstract:**
Essay titled "The Question of Truth" examining truth as correspondence through visual metaphor. Analyzes Aristotle's distinction between material and formal knowledge, arguing truth is property only of judgments/statements requiring commitment. Explores two interpretations of practical knowledge in Aristotle: (1) practical as speculative plus action guided by desire, or (2) practical as fundamentally different, aiming at action not conformity. Argues Aristotle never escaped Plato's speculativism but all genuine knowledge is practical.

**AI Recommendation:** Theoretical essay on truth and practical knowledge; relates to 98-JAN and 98-JUL series.

